caption: Best Sushi in the area by a landslide!
Very clean and welcoming place. They serve big portions and for fair rates. We enjoyed the food very much and the staff were very amiable and informative. Will definitely recommend this place.
I visit this place a lot since I work nearby. I have to say their service is always great and they keep the spot clean constantly. Rates are fair and they serve big portions.

The best sushi spot in nyc! Everything is delicious with unbelievably fresh fish and perfectly made sushi. Good people running this neighborhood mom and pop restaurant. Everything is delicious, even the seaweed salad is better than any other spot.

It's a nice small place that always has fresh sushi; my favorite is the spicy tuna and salmon skin. On top of that, they're nice people who always remember you. However, during Friday and Saturday night they can get quite busy.
(Translated by Google) Excellent value for money, should improve service  (Original) Excelente relación calidad precio, deben mejorar servicio
Sushi was good, the prices were GREAT. You get what you pay for and 3 of us ate for $20!

This place is my number one place.  Of all restaurants I know I favor it most. I always suggests to my friends to go to visit this place. everytime  I I need a fair lunch, this restaurant comes instantly to my head.  Great and   food and a large menu.well mannered crew, and pleasant atmosphere. And very important, the cost is modest. I suggest this spot with no doubt.
What a gem! Try the red rice. Extremely fresh ingredients. I hope this place never leaves.

Sushi here is a 3 star only because the sushi genuinely could be better if they put in alittle more effort. Overall the place is not bad, but if your looking for a night out to eat some sushi...... find somewhere else

I decided to go here after visiting the Brooklyn Bridge Park. A very cosy spot for some decently priced sushi. I would recommend their volcano roll and their spicy tuna roll (I'm a spicy sushi fan clearly). The rolls weren't spicy, but still pretty solid if you're craving sushi in the area. The service was wonderful!
Good food

The best sushi in The Heights. Good kimchi, too.
The place pretends to be Japanese so hard they even act like you insulted their Shogun.

I didn't have high expectations walking in because it was such a tiny, dark, and old place. But the food, ingredients, and the care used in prep was really heartening. Also the amount of food that they gave for the price was amazing NY
It’s in a subway station
It’s a small space inside the Clark street station. Good sushi with very reasonable price.
A New York treasure.  Lovely mom-and-pop sushi restaurant with good food and friendly service.

The food was quite nice and very large portions. The fish was fresh and tasty. The rice isnt sushi rice but all in all the food was good and flavoursome.  A really sweet mom and pop operation. Its only 2 people running the restaurant, from taking orders to making the sushi etc.  So be patient if the restaurant is busy.
Pretty average all around. Won’t be returning since I wasn’t wowed but it’s a decent sushi spot.

(Translated by Google) My favorite sushi restaurant in NY :-) the decor is unspectacular and the location inconspicuous but not only is the sushi is delicious, I go there alone for every NY visit because of the homemade salad dressing. The operators are also very friendly :-)  (Original) Mein lieblings Sushi- Restaurant in NY :-) die Einrichtung ist unspektakulär und die Lage unauffällig aber nicht nur das Sushi is lecker, allein wegen des hausgemachten Salatdressings gehe ich bei jedem NY Besuch dort essen. Die Betreiber sind außerdem auch sehr freundlich :-)
Best sushi in the area. Always super fresh and friendly service. Spicy tune is fabulous.
I live across this place, don’t eat the sushi from outside the store. It can be left in the humidity for quite a while. I got really sick from it and had to go to the hospital...
These guys are so friendly and serve wonderful fish.
Absolutely incredible sushi! The work done by the chefs behind the table was fantastic. I cannot speak highly enough about this place!
The American combo and Nabe Udon are super good. Miso soup is also the right Japanese flavor. A small and cozy place.
Not too pricey, great food
My Favorite  sushi spot. Always Fresh.

Service was a bit slow and overall the sushi here tasted pretty decent. However, one of the things we ordered was "grilled." They have no grill, just a toaster oven that I'm assuming was used to heat up the fish they claimed to have grilled.
Wish I went to other sushi restaurants.  Had sushi sashimi deluxe and shrimp udon.

Very good sushi! High consistency. I've been coming to this place for a few years roughly once or twice a month and they've never once failed to perform. Very highly recommended!!

Delicious really wanna go back. It's a great mom and pop shop that people should give a try perfect for a date or to hang out with a friend.

Real good sushi and rolls!! Go for dinner special, it has all inside!
The rolls were both warm and very loose. The rolls kept falling apart when I tried to eat them with chopsticks, so I had to give up and eat each ingredient separately.

Great mom-and-pop Sushi restaurant, the food is amazing and the atmosphere is great. Just a few tables make this place a very romantic place.
You will have great noodle here. Authentic Japanese-own restaurant. Hand rolls are delicious. Recommend 5 stars.
Not a fan. My edamame was blanketed with salt. The basic rolls that I ordered were overpowered by the amount of mayonnaise used. Tried to force it down to no avail.

I ordered edamame as an appetizer and a spicy tuna roll and a salmon roll. The spicy tuna was a touch too spicy for me, but it was overall very tasty. I would just ask for it without the extra sauce on the top. The salmon roll was virtually flavorless. I suppose I prefer salmon sushi over a roll. Also, I do not generally like it when the nori is on the outside of the roll.  I live down the street, but I will definitely go back and try out other treats on their menu. It was worth it.
located at the clark street subway station - pickup on the way home.
